    "topic": "Important Facts about Tiger Reserves in India 2025",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Key Facts",
        "content": "• Nagarjunsagar-Srisailam is the largest tiger reserve in India, spread over 3296.31 sq km.\n\n• Bandipur National Park in Karnataka was the first tiger reserve in India, established in 1973-74.\n\n• On September 27, 2022, the Uttar Pradesh Cabinet approved the state’s fourth tiger reserve in the Ranipur Wildlife Sanctuary.\n\n• Nagarjunsagar-Srisailam National Park has the largest area under 'Critical Tiger Habitat' in India.\n\n• Guru Ghasidas - Tamor Pingla and Ratapani are among the newest tiger reserves in India."
      }
    ]
